headline: F5 (NASDAQ:FFIV) Delivers Strong Q4 CY2025 Numbers, Stock Jumps 13.3%
summary: Application security provider F5 (NASDAQ:FFIV) reported revenue ahead of Wall Streets expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 7.3% year on year to $822.5 million. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($780 million at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 4.7% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $4.45 per share was 21.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: F5: Fiscal Q1 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The average estimate of seven analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $3.64 per share. The computer networking company posted revenue of $822.5 million in the period, also topping Street forecasts. Six analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $760 million.

headline: Tesla’s Price Target Is Rising Even as Its Profit Outlook Tanks
summary: “Tesla is truly unique in capital markets,” said Nicholas Colas, co-founder at DataTrek Research.  Over the past 12 months, the average forecast for Tesla’s 2026 net income has tumbled 56% from $14.1 billion to $6.1 billion.  The stock is up 7% in that time after closing Tuesday at $435.20, well above Wall Street’s expectations for a year from now.
